The article is a transcript of speeches given during the White House Hanukkah celebration. First Lady Jill Biden welcomes guests and introduces a new menorah made from historic wood from the White House. Rabbi Charlie Cytron-Walker gives a speech expressing gratitude and resilience. President Joe Biden speaks about the significance of Hanukkah and the importance of combating antisemitism. He also discusses the new permanent White House menorah and his administration's efforts to address hate-fueled violence. The President emphasizes the importance of unity and optimism for the future of America. The article concludes with the time the speeches were given.